title: Led Zeppelin - 1969.06.24 London, Maida Vale Studio
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1969.06.24 London, Maida Vale Studio   

JUNE 24 - TOP GEAR, STUDIO 4, MAIDA VALE, LONDON, ENGLAND 
(TUESDAY, recording session between 2:30pm to 9:30pm)

Source: 
Complete superb professional pre-FM radio recording. 18 minutes.

Details: 
The tape is an excellent radio master.

Tracklist:
01 - Whole Lotta Love
02 - Communication Breakdown
03 - What Is And What Should Never Be
04 - Travelling Riverside Blues

Comments: 
Another studio session that needs no recommendation. During this 
short British tour the band was absolutely on peak form and it can 
be easily heard on this amazing recording. A fury, power and energy 
are present on all the tracks. Whole Lotta Love is psychedelic 
stand-out and Robert's yelling during theramin battle is thrilling. 
Communication Breakdown is devastating and What Is And What Should 
Never Be is one of the most dramatic versions the band ever played. 
A real pearl, Traveling Riverside Blues is Zeppelin's bow to the 
talent and magic of Robert Johnson and Plant sings some of his 
"lemon" lyrics
